明天得读神学手册。然后找参考资料，把论文格式搞一下，OK






Holy scripture needs explanation like many other texts, the explanation or interpretation, especially of the Bible, called "exegesis". 

The first method of biblical exegesis called "typology", the interpretation of types and symbols in the Bible. There are three main types or symbols in the Bible: person, such as Moses as the symbol of Christ; event, such as the exodus as the salvation; and institution, such as Israelite as Church. 

Typology was used mainly in the 2nd century by Melito of Sardis in his "Homily on the Passover". He pointed that the Passover is the symbol or the model of the death of Jesus Christ. 

Beside typology, there is another method of biblical exegesis called "allegory". The word "allegory" literarily  means interpreting one thing as another meaning, similar with "typology". 

The difference between "typology" and "allegory" is that "typology" tries to find the common points between the Old Testament and the New Testament. On the contrary, "allegory" uses the Old Testament as a symbol of a religious idea. 

Although there are some small difference between "typology" and "allegory", it's difficult to identify them clearly. Allegory is a more "subjective", more "personal" interpretation of the scripture, but sometimes it can be a graceful way. "Typology" cannot explain all the texts we meet, but "allegory" can, thus preacher will be attracted to use this method. 

According to the saying of Augustine, there are two meanings in the scripture, the meaning of text-flesh-history and the meaning of allegory-mystery-spirit, and sometimes, a text can have both of them. One example is Jerusalem, sometimes points to the earthly Jerusalem, sometimes points to the heavenly Jerusalem, and sometimes points to both the heaven and the earth. 

The standard exegesis method in the middle century called Quadriga, literarily means "four yoked", means the four meanings in scripture. The first one is "textural meaning", the meaning of the text itself. The second one is "allegorical meaning", the another meaning beside the text itself, to preach the doctrine by explaining the obscure texts. The third one is "moral meaning", explaining text to teach about deeds. The fourth one is "apocalyptic meaning", explaining text to point to the future of the fulfillment of God's promise. 

Another exegesis method was from Erasmus, according to his saying, there are "text" and "spirit" in the scripture, that's the external meaning and internal meaning of scripture. The text is shell, and the inside meaning is core, under the text, there is deep meaning. 

In modern times, affected by the enlightenment, there were some exegesis method occurred. The first one is reasonable approaching method, to deny the supernatural events in the scripture, to explain those events in a religious meaning. The second is historical approaching method, use the scripture as a record to explain the origin of Christianity. The third one is dealing with Christianity as a normal religion. The fourth one is dealing the scripture as a literary work. 

Because the Holy Scripture is not a literary work but God's breath, there are some saying about how the Holy Scripture was written. The first one theory thinks the Bible was fully inspired by God's spirit, writer was just a tool. The second one theory thinks the inspiration of the Bible has no difference with the inspiration of arts. The third one theory thinks the inspiration was given by God when reader reading the Bible. 

According to the saying of Calvin, the inspiration of the Bible is accommodated. God inspired those Bible writers to write his word bu accommodated to the level of the people in that age. Someone thinks we can get the revelation without Bible, but Calvin said that the Holy Spirit work through the Bible, thus we need nothing external support. 

Bible and tradition are the two source of our religious life. Tradition means the thing received from older generation. The word tradition in the church means to preach the teaching and the teaching itself. Tradition is an important thing to keep us explain the Bible correctly. 

Gnosticism teaches something strange without the support of tradition, thus let us knowing the importance of tradition. But receive the tradition fully as the age before us is not a good way. In the 20th century, two words was created by Catholic and Orthodox Church, "Tradition" and "Traditionalism", to receive the tradition in a living way. 

Single source theory thinks theology based on the Bible, and tradition means the traditional way of biblical exegesis. But after 14th century, there is another theory called dual-source theory thinks tradition itself is a source of theology, as the second source of revelation. 

Tradition was rejected fully by some ones, they think believers can understand the Bible wholly by the Holy Spirit, and denied many ideas of tradition, such as the doctrine of trinity. 

The most important part of tradition is the ceremony of worship. Gnosticism thinks the flesh is evil, but Irenaeus disagree with them, because the bread, wine and water was used in the holy ceremony of Christianity. Arius thought Jesus as a creature, thus rejected to worship Him, but Athanasius thought the tradition of worship should be considered carefully. And in the age of 1984, some one thinks worship is more important than theology. 

Without tradition, we are easily to make "new things", most of them are wrong, such as the theory of Gnosticism. However, if Jews adhere fully to the tradition, there will be no "new things" occur, even the Son of God will be refused. The word "New Testament" reminded as this is not the old tradition, but the new things created by the Lord. 

Traditionalism is a powerful weapon, yes, it's a weapon for many ones, to attack those men who are not same with us. Jesus was attacked by those Jewish leaders, because Jesus didn't follow their tradition fully, such as the way they observe Sabbath. But there is only One Jesus, most of us should obey the tradition, at least, be carefully with the heart, the purpose of ourselves. 

I'm not sure will I follow Jesus if I was a Jew in the first century, because I'm a little afraid to disobey the tradition, first because I know maybe I'm wrong, and second is that will let me be attacked by others, and those followers of Jesus were indeed attacked by others, even Jesus Himself was attacked by others. I cannot help, but just pray to Jesus, help me to believe in Him. Amen. 















